st_sampler_dispatch.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/harmonic_planner.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `ESCALATIONS.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Correctness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation of `transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> int` correctly computes the smallest semitone offset required to align a sample's detected pitch with the nearest in-key pitch class. It handles the octave wrap correctly by searching in both directions. The tie-breaking logic favors negative transposition, which is consistent and verified by tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+All acceptance criteria are met:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Transposition maps `pitch_hz` to the nearest in-key pitch using the artist's B-rooted palette.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Samples with `pitch_confidence < 0.4` or `pitch_hz <= 0` return 0 semitones, correctly playing \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"atonally\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Tests cover known pitch/key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and octave wrap shortest-path selection.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation leverages `harmonic_planner.py` for canonical key normalization and scale definitions, ensuring consistency with the rest of the SenseWeave harmony engine. The coding style and test patterns match the existing codebase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+No security vulnerabilities were identified. The implementation uses standard math libraries and does not involve unsafe operations or credential handling.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The code is concise, well-documented, and follows idiomatic Python patterns. The tests are comprehensive and use appropriate fixtures (standard within the project). Mandatory hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` were found to be already addressed in the daemon startup flows (`daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- [x] (Minor/Environmental) `pytest tests/ -x` encountered a `PermissionError` in `test_daemon_fallback.py` due to macOS Seatbelt restrictions on `~/.promptclaw/pets.json`. This is an environmental constraint unrelated to the T-019 changes. Focused tests for the new implementation (`tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py`) passed successfully.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation is solid and integrates well with the established harmonic planning utilities. No further actions required for this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+codex\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+I found the existing verifier output saved under a different filename (`...@` with a space). I’ll verify escalation entries for T-019 and then create a fresh report at the exact required path, replacing naming mismatch and reflecting the latest test run.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+exec\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'cd /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw && rg -n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-019|bootstrap_identity|FirstBootAnnouncer|startup\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" ESCALATIONS.md' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ succeeded in 0ms:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+49:- **Details:** `AGENTS.md` asks for architecture/command/startup/changelog updates on orchestration changes, but this task also constrained edits to the bug-fix scope and those doc files already had unrelated local modifications. I limited the change set to the Ollama routing fix plus regression coverage and did not modify the product docs in this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+100:- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer`, which belong to the federation/identity subsystem. This task (self-critique and revision passes for music composition) has no relation to the startup identity flow. No new dependencies requ