itch class with A4-based midi mapping, maps to key/root scale degrees via `harmonic_planner`, and returns the nearest in-key pitch class offset.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The acceptance checklist items are covered in unit tests:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Known pitch/key combinations are tested (e.g., B minor, C major, C5 wrap, octave reuse).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Low-confidence behavior returns zero transposition (`0.39 < 0.4` path).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Edge cases are included for wrap-around and zero pitch.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+However, I did not find a code path where this helper is invoked by the sampler dispatch call chain today; call sites use the `pitch_transpose` parameter directly and pass-through behavior is unchanged.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The helper follows local style and depends on existing `harmonic_planner` primitives used elsewhere, so it is consistent with SenseWeave harmonic conventions. Test placement and naming align with current module-level test patterns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+No security-sensitive operations are introduced. Input handling defaults/munges numeric fields defensively and does not read/write external resources.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Quality of implementation is high for a pure helper and deterministic tests are present. The full project test suite passed: `pip install -e '\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"'.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"'`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- [ ] (Major) `transpose_to_key()` is not currently integrated into the active sampler dispatch pipeline; no caller updates were found in code paths that build sampler events. This means the transposition behavior exists in tests but may not be applied at runtime when samples are selected.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- [x] (Minor/Environmental