sdp/verification/t-020@20260416t054258z-verify.md:13:All seven frequency lanes (sub, bass, low-mid, midrange, upper-mid, presence, air) are defined in `FREQUENCY_LANES` with correct Hz boundaries. `PRODUCTION_ROLE_FREQUENCY_LANES` maps all seven required roles (bass, pad, lead, texture, noise, sample, theramini) to their respective lanes. `_PRODUCTION_METADATA` includes `hpf_hz`, `lpf_hz`, `eq_intent`, and `stereo_policy` for every required role. Both dicts are attached to `MixProfile` as `role_frequency_lanes` and `production_metadata` in `build_mix_profile`. `build_mix_profile` now assigns a `production_role` string to each `VoiceMixTarget` and corrects voice lane boundaries so bass/melody/counter/color no longer overlap. The acceptance criteria are fully met.
