 - Added depth-2 mix-verify end-to-end test coverage (frac-0089): `tests/test_mix_verify.py` now includes `MixVerifyEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/mix_verify.py` public surface through occupied-day mix profile construction, deterministic multi-voice synthetic rendering, profile and mastering validation, LUFS/peak/RMS measurement, clipping/silence checks, low-end and harshness reports, masking checks, render-loudness verification, and JSON-safe diagnostic serialization. `tests/test_test_mix_verify_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production mix verification behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4568 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
